Hi. I'm Italian. I live in Piacenza, 50 km from Bergamo. 33 victims yesterday (March 22), 313 from Feb. 21, in a town of 100K people, 200K with the province.
The most important message is that hospitals aren't the front line, they are the only line!.
Believe me: lockdown, immediately and completely and even if you are no ordered, do it, don't wait! Just 1 month ago we tought it would have never happened here, we were tragically wrong and we are paying it with a coin named "victim", in tousands of samples.
Don't be stupid, arrogant, lazy, ignorant like we were: learn from our mistakes and good examples, you have now much more lessons learned than we had...

The head of a prestigious hospital in Milan just 2 weeks ago said:
"You have a first phase in which you ping your mates saying: "Our neighbor has the problem: ah what a fear! But, at the end, they have it ..."
Then there is the phase in which you realize that it has arrived at your home and in which you reject the idea: "No, it is not possible, it is not possible that it is here among us".
Then there is the phase in which we must take note and measures are taken.
Then there is the phase in which someone says: "But these measures ruin us!", And then they are reduced or postponed.
And then there is the phase of total ruin in which the disease is rampant! "
What stage do you think you are now?
